\b0 \cf0 The increasing availability of protein sequences and key new methodological advances aimed at disentangling direct and indirect co-evolutionary signals have renewed the interest in co-evolution based prediction strategies, with possible applications to a wider range of biological problems, such as the prediction of contacts in protein structures, sites of specific protein interactions, as well as the predictions of protein interaction partners at genomic scale.\
\pard\pardeftab708\ri-198\sl360\slmult1\sa20

